<h2 style="text-align: center;"><strong>Jack Lund Schofield Middle School</strong></h2>
<hr />
<h4 style="text-align: center;">8625 Spencer St.<br /><br /> Las Vegas, NV 89123<br /><br /></h4>
<h4 style="text-align: center;">Principal:&nbsp; Mr. A.J. Adams</h4>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.schofieldms.org">Schofield Middle School Website&nbsp; </a><br /><br /> School Mission Statement</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">At Schofield Middle School we will provide a quality educational environment in which students are encouraged to realize their fullest potential while becoming responsible citizens.<br /><br /><br /> Principal's Message</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">Hello!<br /><br /> I'd like to welcome you to Schofield Middle School's webpage.&nbsp; As you view our pictures and videos, please know that this is only a snapshot of the positive programs that we have to offer.&nbsp; Our goal is to create a positive learning environment with rigorous academic expectations.&nbsp; We enjoy offering multiple student-centered incentives and activities throughout the year.&nbsp; My motto is the "My Kid Standard."&nbsp; What should be good enough for my own children should be good enough for ALL of our students here at Schofield and throughout the CCSD.&nbsp; <br /><br /><br /> About</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">Schofield MS serves over 1300 students each year.&nbsp; We are in a suburb of the city of Las Vegas, only 15 minutes from the strip.&nbsp; We have diverse demographics and pride ourselves in our continual growth in student achievement.<br /><br /> <em>&nbsp;</em><br /><br /> What Our School is Looking For</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">We are looking for people who LIKE kids and want to work with them and teach them to the best of their ability.&nbsp; We can't change the students who walk through our doors, but we can change their attitudes towards education.&nbsp; <br /><br /> <em>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </em><br /><br /> How the Students will Benefit from our School</p>
<hr />
<p style="text-align: center;">You will learn how to cooperatively work with your colleagues and administration to provide the best education possible to our students.&nbsp; You will also learn how to make school fun, and how to make connections with students.<br /><br /> <br />Videos and Pictures</p>
